		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center show-name">
			<h1 class="show-h1">
				Latvia
			</h1>
		</div>
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center show-lesson">
			<h5 class="show-h5">
				Lesson 29
			</h5>
		</div>
			
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<img class="show-flag" src="https://cdn.britannica.com/49/6249-004-D8906A92/Flag-Latvia.jpg">
		</div>
		
		<div class='d-flex justify-content-center show-firstquickfacth4'>
			<h4>Capital: Riga</h4>
		</div>
		
		<div class='d-flex justify-content-center show-quickfactsh4'>
			<h4>Population: 1.9 million</h4>
		</div>
		
		<div class='d-flex justify-content-center show-quickfactsh4'>
			<h4>Gross Domestic Product (GDP): 34 billion dollars</h4>
		</div>
		
		<div class='d-flex justify-content-center show-quickfactsh4'>
			<h4>Gross Domestic Product (GDP) Per Capita: 18,000 dollars</h4>
		</div>
		
		
		
		<hr class="show-hr1">	
		
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<figure>
				<img class="show-img1 show-map" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/9/9b/Latvia_in_Europe.svg">
				<span class="d-flex justify-content-center">
				</span>
			</figure>
		</div>
		
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				The Republic of Latvia lies south of Estonia in the Baltic Region of Eastern Europe. After being ruled by the Swedish and Russians for centuries, Latvia finally established their independence in 1918. However, during the second World War, Latvia was invaded by Germany. Almost a third of all Latvian citizens were killed during the Nazi invasion. After the war, Latvia was forced into joining the Soviet Union. In 1991, Latvia broke free from the USSR and reestablished itself as the Republic of Latvia.


			</p>
		</div>
		
		

		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<figure>
				<img class="show-img1" src="https://www.state.gov/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Latvia-2107x1406.jpg">
				<span class="d-flex justify-content-center">
					<em><figcaption>Riga, Latvia</figcaption></em>
				</span>
			</figure>
		</div>
		
		
		
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				Despite many centuries of foreign invasion, Latvia maintained its identity through their cultural and musical traditions. Today, Latvia is a peaceful country with and advanced economy offering good living standards to its people, 40% of which are ethnic.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<figure>
				<img class="show-img1" src="https://mediad.publicbroadcasting.net/p/wmuk/files/styles/x_large/public/201803/LatvianSongFest_Matisons.jpg">
				<span class="d-flex justify-content-center">
					<em><figcaption>Latvia retained its cultural and musical traditions throughout the centuries</figcaption></em>
				</span>
			</figure>
		</div>
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				Latvia has temperate weather with mild winters and humid summers. Latvia contains 12,000 rivers within it's borders. Wide ranges of forests take up 56% of the land.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<figure>
				<img class="show-img1" src="https://www.drax.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/AdobeStock_294690820-1024x640.jpeg">
				<span class="d-flex justify-content-center">
					<em><figcaption>Forests make up 56% of the land in Latvia</figcaption></em>
				</span>
			</figure>
		</div>
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				The capital, Riga, is the largest city with over 600,000 inhabitants. Riga is considered to be a cultural center, and contains many museums. The Old Town section of the city is a pedestrian only tourist area filled with restaurants and shops.
			</p>
		</div>
	
	
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<figure>
				<img class="show-img1" src="https://www.treksplorer.com/wp-content/uploads/colourful-building-old-town-riga-latvia.jpg">
				<span class="d-flex justify-content-center">
					<em><figcaption>Vecrīga, the Old Town section of Riga, is the historical center of Latvia's capital</figcaption></em>
				</span>
			</figure>
		</div>
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<h3 class="show-factsh3">
				Two unique facts about Latvia
			</h3>
		</div>
			
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				Crocodile Dundee, a famous movie character from the 1980’s, was a Latvian who moved to Australia after World War Two and became a crocodile hunter. He was known as Crocodile Harry, and reportedly killed over 40,000 crocodiles!
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				The Latvian Song and Dance Festival has been held every five years since 1873. In the latest event in 2018, 16,000 people sang Latvian folk songs without any musical accompaniment!
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<figure>
				<img class="show-img1" src="https://static.dw.com/image/16909012_101.jpg">
				<span class="d-flex justify-content-center">
					<em><figcaption>The Latvian Song and Dance Festival in Riga, Latvia</figcaption></em>
				</span>
			</figure>
		</div>
		
		
		
		
